Description ✨ 2024 Mazda CX-90 3.3 Turbo Premium AWD – Luxury, Power, and Versatility in One

🚀 Smooth Turbocharged Power – Enjoy a refined yet powerful 3.3L turbo engine with mild-hybrid support for seamless acceleration and enhanced fuel efficiency.
🛞 i-ACTIV AWD Confidence – Intelligent all-wheel drive keeps you in control, rain 🌧️ or shine ☀️ — perfect for Pacific Northwest adventures.
🛋️ Premium Comfort – Leather-trimmed seats, heated front and rear seating, and a panoramic moonroof 🌙 make every drive a joy.
🎶 Next-Level Tech – 12.3" full-color display, Apple CarPlay & Android Auto 📱, Bose® premium audio system 🎵, and wireless phone charging 🔋.
🛡️ Advanced Safety – Includes Mazda Radar Cruise Control 🚗, lane-keep assist, blind spot monitoring 👀, and 360° camera view 📷 for added peace of mind.
👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 3 Rows, 7 Seats – Room for the whole family or group trip with flexible cargo space 🧳.

Optional Add-Ons Available for Your Trip:
🛣️ Toll Pass (Portable) – Drive on WA-520 Bridge, I-405 Express Lanes, and SR-167 HOT lanes worry-free. Save time and enjoy discounted tolls.
🎒 One-Way Airport Dropoff – Choose pickup or return anywhere within 5 miles of SeaTac ✈️ for added flexibility.
👶 Child Seat Available – Traveling with little ones? Request a forward-facing or booster seat for extra peace of mind.
📦 Luggage Rack / Cargo Carrier – Need more space? Add a rooftop solution for your gear (based on availability).

❇️ SEA airport terminal garage pick-up and drop-off available (parking fee applied)
❇️ Contactless pick-up and drop-off. Meet in person if requested.
❇️ My cars are available for INSTANT BOOKING. 20mins last-minute booking available. 
❇️ My cars are always clean and well-prepared for you.
❇️ We accept all trip modifications, even if it means giving a refund!
❇️ Our Airport free parking lot,  Pick up /Drop off  0.7 miles from the airport. 
 You can Uber here from Seatac Airport just $10-$16
🅿️ The renter is responsible for covering the fee at the SeaTac Airport parking garage. The cost for General Parking is a flat $37 per day. You pay for the Airport. Not go though to us or Turo.

Thank you for choosing our vehicle! To ensure a smooth and enjoyable experience for both you and future guests, please review and follow these guidelines:

⛽ Fuel
⏩ Please return the vehicle with the same fuel level as when picked up (usually full).
💵 A refueling charge will apply if the car is returned with less gas.

🧼 Cleanliness
🧽 Please return the car in the same clean condition as received.
🧺 Light dirt is expected, but excessive mess (e.g. sand, pet hair, smoke, spills) may result in a cleaning fee.

🚭 No Smoking
🚫 Absolutely no smoking or vaping inside the vehicle.
🧾 A smoke removal fee of up to $250 may be charged if detected.

🐶 Pets
🐾 Pets are allowed with prior approval only.
🧹 Please clean up after your pet to avoid cleaning fees.

⏰ Timeliness
📲 If you need more time, request a trip extension through the app before the trip ends.
💸 Late returns may result in late fees per Turo policy.

📍 Toll Roads & Tickets
🛣️ If you selected the toll pass add-on, you’re welcome to use express lanes and toll bridges.
📮 If not, please avoid toll lanes or expect to cover tolls and processing fees.
🧾 All parking, traffic, or speeding tickets incurred during your trip are your responsibility.

🛑 Prohibited Use
❌ No track driving, off-roading, racing, towing, or using the vehicle for delivery/rideshare (Uber, Lyft, etc.).
Turo will not cover any damages or incidents from prohibited use.

🧳 Lost & Found
🎒 Please double-check for personal items before returning the vehicle. We are not responsible for items left behind, but will do our best to help return them. More FAQs ❄️ Do I need snow chains for trips near Seattle during winter? 🏔️ From October to May, snow chains are required or strongly recommended when traveling to areas like Leavenworth, Mount Rainier, national parks, or Canada — even for AWD vehicles. Please check local DOT and park regulations before your trip to ensure compliance and safety. 🇨🇦 Can I drive the car to Canada? Yes, you're welcome to take the vehicle into Canada! 🇨🇦
We just ask that you please add the “Unlimited Distance” extra at checkout to cover the additional mileage.
It ensures you can enjoy the trip without worrying about overage fees.

Let me know if you have any questions or need help adding it! 🚧 Q: Do I need to pay for tolls? Tolls are not included by default. If you plan to use toll roads or bridges, please add the “Portable GPS” extra — it includes a toll pass with discounted rates.
✅ With this extra, you're allowed to use:

SR-520 Floating Bridge

Tacoma Narrows Bridge

I-405 & SR-167 express lanes

❌ Without this extra, you are not authorized to use these toll routes.
Any fines or fees from unauthorized toll usage will be your responsibility and submitted as a reimbursement through Turo. Trinity RPM's response Appreciate your feedback. Just to clarify — this vehicle has never had any smoking violation( Turo pay $150 for it), and no odor concerns were mentioned during your trip. Your review came only after a fuel reimbursement was processed. Although the car was returned without refueling and in less-than-clean condition, we still chose to leave you a 5-star guest review. For future guests with scent sensitivities, we’re happy to offer one of our many brand-new vehicles — just let us know in advance. Mike • June 21, 2025 The 2024 CX-90 was an absolute pleasure to drive—smooth, powerful, and packed with great features. Easily one of the best cars I’ve rented on Turo! The hosts were just as great—communication was clear and quick, and pickup/drop-off couldn’t have been easier. Highly recommend both the vehicle and the hosts. Would definitely rent again!
